Motivation

Being able to accurately predict how many people will attend Crown Casino (Melbourne) food and beverage outlets is useful for optimising resource allocation. A forecasting model was thus built for 'Covers' (number of restaurant attendees) which can be generalised to all major outlets. The data isn't uploaded for privacy.

In[]:
#Exemplar outlet data

from IPython.display import Image, display
display(Image(filename='Diamond_Bar_Covers.png'))

Strategy

  1. Predictors: Intra-day seasonality, weekly seasonality, yearly seasonality, short term linear trend and long term linear trend.
  2. Model Type: Either Ridge or Lasso regression (customised to account for public holiday attendance) was fit at each outlet.

Results

Median forecast accuracy of 80% accross outlets.
